@BoozleBAM I know this could and most times goes without saying but make sure you do a “save as” for a separate session before you start flexing and editing your drums. Like @Slow Hand said, you can easily edit the life out of a performance and it’s good to 
1) be able to go back to how you recorded it exactly if you mess up and start chasing your tail (I’ve been there) 
2) it’s good to just be able to a/b as a gut check
